               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0157DDM">Dändera Dabra Mǝḥrat Mikāʾel / DDM</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1800" notAfter="1850">First half of 19th cent. according
                        to the palaeographic features of the handwriting (Text I and Text II). 
                        Additio 1 mentions Metropolitan Krǝstodolu (in tenure 1720-1735) and King
                        Dāwit III (r. 1716-21), but the text is obviously a late addition written on
                        the protective leaves of the Ms., and the scribe copied the names from the
                        model manuscript.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>On the incipit of Text I (3r), the name ʾabuna Gabra
                     Krǝstos is crudely added in pencil (following the words mǝslä
                     gäbru...). Currently the Ms. is in private possession of
                     priest (qäšši) Tasfāy ʾAbrǝha.</provenance></history>
